12 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Department of
Commerce; making an appropriation to the Pandemic
13 Relief Primary Source Revolving Fund; identifying
source; establishing amounts; providing purposes;
14 requiring and limiting the utilization of funds;
authorizing certain memorandums of understanding;
15 limiting scope; prohibiting certain memoranda terms;
authorizing and limiting the promulgation of rules
16 and utilization of procedures; requiring certain
reports and submissions to certain entities;
17 requiring appearance before certain joint committee;
limiting duration of certain requirements; providing
18 determination process; providing for noncodification;
and declaring an emergency.
19
20
21
22 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
23 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
24 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
Req. No. 17514 Page 1

1 There is hereby appropriated to the Pandemic Relief Primary
2 Source Revolving Fund from any monies not otherwise appropriated
3 from the Statewide Recovery Fund established in Section 255 of Title
4 62 of the Oklahoma Statutes, the sum of Twenty-one Million Six
5 Hundred Forty Thousand Ninety-one Dollars ($21,640,091.00) or so
6 much thereof as may be necessary for award by the Oklahoma
7 Department of Commerce through grants to enhance industrial parks,
8 airparks, and ports to cover costs related to water, wastewater,
9 sewer, and broadband projects eligible under the provisions of the
10 American Rescue Plan Act of 2021 that support sites or surrounding
11 communities identified by the Department as having such needs prior
12 to the passage of this act and as discussed in the Transportation,
13 Infrastructure, and Rural Development Working Group. Such funds
14 shall be utilized in a manner consistent with the recommendations
15 adopted by the Joint Committee on Pandemic Relief Funding on April
16 15, 2026.
17 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
18 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
19 The Oklahoma Department of Commerce may enter into memorandums
20 of understanding with other agencies of the State of Oklahoma for
21 the auditing, documentation, evaluation, implementation, oversight,
22 reporting, and management of funds and associated efforts related to
23 the appropriations made in this act; provided, that no such
24 memorandum of understanding shall require or include, as an option
Req. No. 17514 Page 2

1 or c ondition, the direct or practical transfer or relinquishment of
2 control by the agency appropriated such funds to budget, expend,
3 allocate, and request the distribution of the funds appropriated by
4 this act.
5 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
6 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
7 The Oklahoma Department of Commerce may promulgate rules,
8 utilize existing rules, establish procedures, and utilize existing
9 procedures to implement the provisions of this act; provided, such
10 rules and procedures do not conflict with or impede the provisions
11 of this act.
12 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
13 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
14 A. The Oklahoma Department of Commerce shall:
15 1. Submit to the Chairs of the Joint Committee on Pandemic
16 Relief Funding, or any successor Oklahoma House of Representatives
17 or Oklahoma State Senate legislative committee or joint committee,
18 as designated by the Speaker of the Oklahoma House of
19 Representatives and the President Pro Tempore of the Oklahoma State
20 Senate:
21 a. a written or electronic quarterly report detailing the
22 budgeting, expenditure, and management of all monies
23 appropriated in this act, and
24
Req. No. 17514 Page 3

1 b. a copy of all memorandums of understanding and
2 contracts with third parties entered into by the
3 Oklahoma Department of Commerce to facilitate, assist,
4 or administer powers and duties provided to the
5 Department under the provisions of this act; and
6 2. At the Joint Committee on Pandemic Relief Funding's request,
7 appear before the Joint Committee no later than six (6) months after
8 the effective date of this act, and as otherwise requested by the
9 Joint Committee, to provide a status update regarding the
10 implementation of the provisions of this act.
11 B. The provisions of subsection A of this section shall remain
12 applicable for the period of time that monies appropriated under
13 this act are being budgeted, expended, or managed in the state. The
14 ending of such period shall be determined by the State Treasurer,
15 and shall be reported to the Governor, the Speaker of the Oklahoma
16 House of Representatives and the President Pro Tempore of the
17 Oklahoma State Senate.
18 SECTION 5. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
19 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
20 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
21 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
